<subSubSection id="C370650EFFC4FFD2FF29F8DBBC85C8E6" pageId="23" pageNumber="244" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD53685FFC4FFD2FF29F8DBBC85C8E6" blockId="23.[136,1451,1846,2089]" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC4FFD2FF29F8DBBE29C856" bold="true" box="[136,284,1846,1872]" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Description:</emphasis>
— 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC4FFD2FE99F8DABEF8C857" box="[312,461,1847,1873]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Spermogonia</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC4FFD2FDA4F8DABD77C856" box="[517,578,1847,1872]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">aecia</emphasis>
not found. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC4FFD2FD64F8DBBC1CC856" box="[709,809,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Uredinia</emphasis>
rarely found. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC4FFD2FC6BF8DBBB43C856" box="[970,1142,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Urediniospores</emphasis>
20.5–25.0 × 17.5–21.5 µm (av. 23.0 × 19.5 µm); walls, 1.4–2.2 µm (av. 1.7 µm). 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC4FFD2FCAAF8B7BC77C872" box="[779,834,1882,1908]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Telia</emphasis>
amphigenous, compact, black, erumpent. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC4FFD2FA8DF8B7BA9EC872" box="[1324,1451,1882,1908]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="244">Teliospores</emphasis>
broadly clavate, ellipsoid, mostly conical or rounded at apices, constricted at the septa, attenuate at the bases, 41.0– 55.5 × 15.0–20.0 µm (49.5 × 17.5 µm); walls brown, 0.6–1.3 µm (av. 0.9 µm) thick at sides, 6.0–10.7 µm (av. 8.3 µm) at apices; pedicels persistent, hyaline, 20.5–49.5 µm (av. 30.5 µm) long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
