</taxonomicName>
(D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C370650EFFCBFFDDFF1CFCDCBBF1CB41" pageId="24" pageNumber="245" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD53685FFCBFFDDFF1CFCDCBBF1CB41" blockId="24.[136,1452,780,1095]" pageId="24" pageNumber="245">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFCBFFDDFF1CFCDCBFCACC4D" bold="true" box="[189,255,817,843]" pageId="24" pageNumber="245">Note:</emphasis>
—The two cited specimens on 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFCBFFDDFDFEFCDCBD97CC4D" box="[607,674,817,843]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="245" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFCBFFDDFDFEFCDCBD97CC4D" box="[607,674,817,843]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="245">Carex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are phylogenetically clustered together with 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFCBFFDDFB00FCDCBA28CC4C" box="[1185,1309,817,842]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="245">
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFCBFFDDFB00FCDCBA2CCC4C" box="[1185,1305,817,842]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="24" pageNumber="245" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="urticata">P. urticata</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
although no spermogonial and aecial specimen on 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFCBFFDDFDE0FCB8BDBFCC68" box="[577,650,853,878]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Urtica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="24" pageNumber="245" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFCBFFDDFDE0FCB8BDBFCC68" box="[577,650,853,878]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="245">Urtica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been collected. The telial stage is morphologically similar to the descriptions of this species by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFCBFFDDFE40FC94BD5ECC95" author="Kern, F. D." box="[481,619,889,915]" pageId="24" pageNumber="245" pagination="205 - 238" refId="ref20551" refString="Kern, F. D. (1917) Noth American species of Puccinia on Carex. Mycologia 9: 205 - 238." type="journal article" year="1917">Kern (1917)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFCBFFDDFD00FC94BB3BCC95" author="Termorshuizen, A. J. &amp; Swertz, C. A." box="[673,1038,889,915]" pageId="24" pageNumber="245" refId="ref21591" refString="Termorshuizen, A. J. &amp; Swertz, C. A. (2011) Dutch rust fungi. Aad Termorsguizen, Netherland." type="book" year="2011">Termorshuizen &amp; Swertz (2011)</bibRefCitation>
, although the teliospores are slightly smaller. Because only a few specimens have been collected the distribution of this species is suspected to be limited to the study area. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFCBFFDDFE8CFC2CBEC5CCDC" box="[301,496,961,986]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="24" pageNumber="245" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="urticata">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFCBFFDDFE8CFC2CBEC5CCDC" box="[301,496,961,986]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="245">Puccinia urticata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been treated as 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFCBFFDDFD68FC2CBC1ACCDC" box="[713,815,961,986]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="24" pageNumber="245" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caricis">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFCBFFDDFD68FC2CBC1ACCDC" box="[713,815,961,986]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="245">P. caricis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFCBFFDDFCF3FC2CBCFCCCDC" box="[850,969,961,986]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="24" pageNumber="245" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caricina">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFCBFFDDFCF3FC2CBCFCCCDC" box="[850,969,961,986]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="245">P. caricina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
